+## Paired n-gram paged-greedy parity gate
+
+`spec_decode_paired_parity_gate.py` is a correctness gate, not a benchmark. It
+launches a fresh target-only paged-greedy process and a fresh n-gram
+paged-greedy process for every arm and repeat, compares token IDs exactly, and
+writes a non-overwritable pass/fail receipt. It records no timings and makes no
+speed claim.
+
+The model must be bound to a full Hugging Face commit SHA. The corpus and
+optional prefix-cache history use strict JSONL records with exactly these two
+fields:
+
+```json
+{"request_id":"request-001","prompt":"A deterministic prompt"}
+```
+
+The standard gate always includes C1 and C16 plus the K=1 n-gram control. A
+history file is replayed in every fresh engine and must produce a real measured
+paged-cache hit; use `none` to bind a deliberately cold, cache-disabled run.
+
+```bash
+PYTHONPATH=$PWD python tools/spec_decode_paired_parity_gate.py \
+  --model Qwen/Qwen3-0.6B \
+  --model-revision <full-40-character-hf-commit-sha> \
+  --corpus /absolute/path/pinned_requests.jsonl \
+  --prefix-cache-history /absolute/path/pinned_prefix_history.jsonl \
+  --concurrency 1,16 --ngram-k 1,3 --repeats 3 \
+  --output-json /absolute/path/paired_ngram_parity.json
+```
+
+## Historical C1/K3 divergence diagnostic
+
+`reproduce_historical_c1_ngram_divergence.py` is intentionally separate from
+the production parity gate. It loads the *installed pre-fallback wheel* in
+fresh isolated child processes and tries to reproduce the known July 2026 C1
+K=3 token divergence. The retained server launch had prefix caching disabled,
+so cache state is explicitly not treated as its cause or its safety predicate.
+It is a negative regression diagnostic: it records no timing, cannot qualify a
+speedup, and a PASS means the unsafe old topology was reproduced.
+
+It replays `sonnet-000` through `sonnet-011` with their original 150-token
+continuations, then measures only `sonnet-012` through token 92 (93 tokens).
+The full fixture corpus remains SHA-bound; the bounded target is sufficient
+because token 92 is the first known mismatch. The tool requires two
+ABBA-alternated baseline/candidate pairs, active K=3 drafts, stable repeats,
+and the exact signature: baseline token 1875 versus pre-fallback n-gram token
+702 at zero-based output index 92. It binds the recovered cache-disabled
+direct-engine profile, but cannot by itself certify or falsify the original
+OpenAI-server topology.
+
+```bash
+PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \
+  .venv-vllm-metal/bin/python -B \
+  tools/reproduce_historical_c1_ngram_divergence.py \
+  --model /absolute/path/to/mlx-community-Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-4bit \
+  --model-revision 08231374eeacb049a0eade7922910865b8fce912 \
+  --fixture-manifest .artifacts/cx-inference/sonnet-c1-regression/fixture.json \
+  --history .artifacts/cx-inference/sonnet-c1-regression/history.jsonl \
+  --corpus .artifacts/cx-inference/sonnet-c1-regression/corpus.jsonl \
+  --output-json /absolute/path/new-c1-k3-diagnostic.json
+```
